## Page 11: References & Tools

### Free (no key or fully local in practice)

- React official docs – Core concepts, hooks, and modern patterns for building React frontends.  
  https://react.dev  

- Vite – Fast dev server and build tool commonly used for modern React apps.  
  https://vitejs.dev  

- Netlify (static sites) – Free tier for small React SPAs; Git-based deploys, simple config.  
  https://www.netlify.com  

- Vercel (static/frontends) – Free tier well-suited to React and Next.js frontends.  
  https://vercel.com  

- GitHub Pages – Free static hosting for React builds from Git repos.  
  https://pages.github.com  

- Cloudflare Pages – Free static deployment platform for JAMstack/React apps.  
  https://pages.cloudflare.com  

- Pollinations.ai – Key-less AI media generation endpoints suitable for experiments and demos.  
  https://pollinations.ai  

- Ollama – Run open models locally and expose a local HTTP API to your React app.  
  https://ollama.com  

- Free-LLM resource list – Community‑maintained index of free LLM inference endpoints and hosts.  
  https://github.com/cheahjs/free-llm-api-resources  

- AI SDK (TypeScript toolkit) – Open SDK for calling multiple AI backends from TypeScript/React.  
  https://ai-sdk.dev  


### Free‑tier (requires account / key but usable at zero cost for small projects)

- Hugging Face Inference API – Hosted open models (text, vision, more) with a free quota.  
  https://huggingface.co/inference-api  

- Google Gemini / AI Studio – Text and multimodal models with generous free usage caps.  
  https://ai.google.dev  

- Multi‑model AI aggregators (e.g. OpenRouter, AIMLAPI) – Route to multiple providers with free credits/tiers.  
  https://openrouter.ai  
  https://aimlapi.com  

- “Top free AI APIs” overviews – Curated lists of up‑to‑date free and free‑tier AI APIs.  
  https://aicurator.io/free-ai-apis/  
  https://ucscode.com/top-free-apis-for-your-projects-is-chatgpts-api-really-free-and-other-ai-options/  

- Guides to free AI APIs and tools – Broad surveys of free tools and APIs (LLMs, vision, etc.).  
  https://www.datacamp.com/blog/free-ai-tools  
  https://eesel.ai/blog/free-ai-api  

- Free React hosting roundups – Comparisons of free React hosting options and deployment flows.  
  https://blog.logrocket.com/9-ways-deploy-react-app-free/  
  https://animaapp.com/blog/industry/8-free-react-app-hosting-services 

